Antennula (
Fig. 3F
) relative length ratios of articles 1.0, 0.70, 0.33, 0.33, 0.33, 0.33, L/W ratios of articles 1.5, 2.0, 1.0, 1.0, 2.0, 2.0. Article 1 with one simple seta. Article 2 with one simple seta. Article 4 with two simple setae. Article 6 with two aesthetascs, aesthetascs simple, tubular. Antenna (
Fig. 3F
) length 0.18 body length. Ischium angular with medial projection, about as long as coxa. Merus about as long as coxa, basis, and ischium together, articulating distolaterally on ischium, antennal proximodistal axis with distinctly sharp bend. Carpus longer than merus, articulating distolaterally on merus, antennal proximodistal axis with distinctly sharp bend between merus and carpus. Flagellum with eight articles and two to six short setae distally on each article.

